<br>
Having seen the movie, I was curious about how one goes about reading the old comic book history.  I know the original comic books are collectables, and a whole X-men collection would be quite out of my budget.  Does Marvel reprint the older comic books in some format that wouldn't bankrupt me?<br>
<br>
Brevis<br>
Used to read Groo <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jaelyndimathe>Jaelyn DiMathe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Truth</span><br>  Posts: 481<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/12/03 2:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1507.topic&index=46>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://myweb.cableone.net/agunders/jae.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: X-Men 2</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Does Marvel reprint the older comic books in some format that wouldn't bankrupt me?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Quite sometime ago, they started to reprint from the original series in a title called &quot;Classic X-Men.&quot;  Not sure how far they went, or how much of the original series they covered, but back issues would be less expensive than the originals.  As for bound volumes, not sure if they ever released them.    However, if you're looking at purchasing the actual x-men comics, you'll go broke.  They cost quite the pretty penny now (plus aren't there about 25 X-titles total past/present you'd have to pick up given all the story arcs?).  My advice would be to start at issue 210 (think that starts the mutant massacre) and read from there on.  Most of the important recent story changes start about then, and will lay down most of the background story for you (just pick up X-factor and New Mutants to fill in the cross-overs).<br>
