<br>
What I liked was the use of Professor X as a weapon here, which happened recently in the Cassandra Nova story arc.  <br>
<br>
Not sure how much I like Patrick Stewart's Prof. X, though.  I know back when an &quot;X-Men&quot; movie was just a list of fan's picks for who they'd have play the characters in the letter's section of comics, everyone always wanted him, he's ok I guess, I just keep expecting him to turn to Cyclops and say &quot;Make it so&quot;.<br>
<br>
They never touched on the fact that Mystique is Nightcrawler's mother, that would have been nice.<br>
<br>
One way to think about it, is the movie universe is just another separate universe from the comic book's storyline.  Sort of like with the &quot;Ultimates&quot; if you're a comic book reader.<br>
Just adding a twist, a remix if you will.  Marvel does this all the time, it adds some flavor and allows you to see the characters develop under a new set of circumstances.<br>
